[2026-01-01] Started LLD practice journey. Set up repo with README and project roadmap.
[2026-01-02T09:15:00+05:30] ParkingLot day1: Created Vehicle (2W/4W/Large), ParkingSpot (type/status), ParkingLot entity with floor layout.
[2026-01-03T11:00:00+05:30] ParkingLot day2: Added ParkingSpotRepository and VehicleRepository interfaces + HashMap-based impls.
[2026-01-04T10:45:00+05:30] ParkingLot day3: ParkingLotService finds nearest available spot, issues Ticket, updates spot status on entry/exit.
[2026-01-06T09:30:00+05:30] ParkingLot day4: ParkingLotController orchestrates park/unpark flow. Simulation shows 3-floor parking lot.
[2026-01-07T20:00:00+05:30] ParkingLot day5: Added HourlyFeeStrategy, DailyFeeStrategy. PaymentAdapter wraps external payment gateway.
[2026-01-09T10:00:00+05:30] Notes: Documented Parking Lot design, UML class diagram, how Strategy pattern separates fee algorithms.
[2026-01-10T09:00:00+05:30] ATM day1: Created ATM, Account, Card, Session, Transaction domain classes. Added Denomination enum and CashDrawer.
[2026-01-11T11:30:00+05:30] ATM day2: State pattern impl - ATMState interface, AbstractATMState base, IdleState/CardInsertedState/AuthenticatedState.
[2026-01-12T10:15:00+05:30] ATM day3: Completed full state machine with remaining 3 states. Each state validates allowed operations.
[2026-01-13T09:45:00+05:30] ATM day4: Strategy pattern for transactions. WithdrawalStrategy uses greedy algorithm on CashDrawer denominations.
[2026-01-15T10:30:00+05:30] ATM day5: Added 7 repository interfaces + impl classes (ATM, Account, Card, Session, Transaction, CashDrawer, AdminUser).
[2026-01-16T09:00:00+05:30] ATM day6: Service layer wired with repositories. PIN validation, session timeout, concurrent transaction guard.
[2026-01-17T11:00:00+05:30] ATM day7: Controller layer delegates to services. AdminController handles cash refill and ATM maintenance mode.
[2026-01-18T10:00:00+05:30] ATM day8: ATMSimulation demonstrates insert card -> PIN auth -> select withdrawal -> dispense cash -> eject card flow.
[2026-01-19T20:30:00+05:30] ATM refactor: Moved denomination greedy logic into CashDrawer. Added InvalidATMOperationException for error cases.
[2026-01-21T09:30:00+05:30] Elevator day1: Elevator entity with currentFloor/direction/status. ElevatorRequest with source/destination floors.
[2026-01-22T10:00:00+05:30] Elevator day2: ElevatorScheduler uses SCAN algorithm - services requests in one direction before reversing.
[2026-01-23T11:15:00+05:30] Elevator day3: ElevatorRepository and RequestRepository with PriorityQueue-based pending request storage.
[2026-01-24T09:00:00+05:30] Elevator day4: ElevatorService picks optimal elevator (least distance) for each floor request.
[2026-01-25T10:45:00+05:30] Elevator day5: 10-floor, 3-elevator simulation. ElevatorController manages button presses inside/outside cabin.
[2026-01-26T20:00:00+05:30] Notes: Added elevator section to LEARNING_NOTES. Key insight: SCAN = disk scheduling applied to vertical movement.
[2026-01-28T09:15:00+05:30] Hotel day1: Created full domain model - Room (Standard/Deluxe/Suite), Booking with state machine, Guest profile.
[2026-01-29T10:30:00+05:30] Hotel day2: Room.isAvailableForDates() checks overlapping bookings. Booking validates check-in before check-out.
[2026-01-30T09:00:00+05:30] Hotel day3: HotelRepository, RoomRepository, GuestRepository, BookingRepository + impls with date-range queries.
[2026-01-31T11:00:00+05:30] Hotel day4: Services handle room locking on booking, automated room release on check-out, late checkout fees.
[2026-02-01T10:00:00+05:30] Hotel day5: PaymentService calculates stay duration, applies seasonal pricing, generates itemized invoice.
[2026-02-03T09:30:00+05:30] Hotel day6: HotelController, BookingController, RoomController handle HTTP-like command routing.
[2026-02-04T10:45:00+05:30] Hotel day7: End-to-end simulation: guest registers -> books suite -> checks in -> checks out -> invoice.
[2026-02-05T09:00:00+05:30] Notes: Documented Hotel design. Booking state: Pending->Confirmed->CheckedIn->CheckedOut->Cancelled.
[2026-02-06T11:00:00+05:30] TaskMgmt day1: Task with priority (LOW/MED/HIGH/CRITICAL), assignee, dueDate, tags, subtasks, comments.
[2026-02-07T10:30:00+05:30] TaskMgmt day2: TaskState machine (TODO->IN_PROGRESS->REVIEW->DONE). Only assigned user can move to IN_PROGRESS.
[2026-02-09T09:15:00+05:30] TaskMgmt day3: TaskRepository supports queries: findByAssignee, findByPriority, findOverdue, findByProject.
[2026-02-10T10:00:00+05:30] TaskMgmt day4: Full service layer. TaskService enforces role-based permission checks (Admin/Manager/Dev roles).
[2026-02-11T09:45:00+05:30] TaskMgmt day5: Demo: Manager creates sprint, assigns tasks to devs, devs update progress, manager reviews.
[2026-02-12T11:30:00+05:30] TaskMgmt day6: TaskSubscriber (Observer) notifies users via event bus on assignment, status change, overdue trigger.
